<p>Madagascar&#x27;s President Andry Rajoelina said he left the country for a &quot;safe place&quot; after an elite military unit joined weeks of youth-led protests demanding his resignation [theguardian.com#4][euronews.com#21]. Reports said he was evacuated by a French aircraft, though officials have not confirmed this [aljazeera.com#7][bbc.com#20]. In a video address, Rajoelina called for dialogue and said the constitution should be respected, adding there had been assassination attempts since September 25; he has not resigned and described events as an attempted coup [npr.org#3][france24.com#17][apnews.com#22]. Authorities and witnesses report at least 22 people have been killed during the unrest over the past three weeks [washingtonpost.com#8]. On Tuesday, Rajoelina announced he had dissolved the National Assembly, deepening the political standoff [straitstimes.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/xDLyD8hcZUjJRfmQ-4uATzvs149v_P_Mgj1FVnutq352S6Q7nA0TKH3UBEvRX_LSVD5g7xxpX1Ta0312yIaY3EQcYvaU2cLGFgNCyDiyJs69SnnXQsBXXQpgV0UNlC-mpumkleea-XCSciXzMoh8kkR50V7-w3DcRCncMp0e3a8RcZp-5q8j5VOgu4m3uEZe-BflSD1L9q6LN8jpehdxa7bSt-Ca4n6TWVGwKdvuDwOKIMPogGoP5Yf5nINbz8ykDNjoPDTZeO3wu0YX3A' alt='Youth-led protesters rally in Antananarivo as political tensions rise in Madagascar.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Military shift: The elite CAPSAT unit sided with protesters and urged the president and ministers to step down [euronews.com#21][theguardian.com#4].</li><li>Casualties reported: At least 22 people have been killed in three weeks of unrest, according to local authorities and witnesses [washingtonpost.com#8].</li><li>Constitutional call: Rajoelina urged dialogue and respect for the constitution, stating there were attempts on his life since September 25 [npr.org#3][france24.com#17].</li><li>Assembly dissolved: Rajoelina dissolved Madagascar’s National Assembly amid the escalating standoff [straitstimes.com#1].</li><li>French link: He reportedly left aboard a French aircraft, and France’s president offered support, according to French media [aljazeera.com#7][bbc.com#20][lemonde.fr#13].</li></ul><blockquote>To find a way out of this situation - Andry Rajoelina</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>President Andry Rajoelina: He says he moved to a safe location after assassination attempts, calls for dialogue and constitutional procedures, and rejects calls to resign. (<a href='https://www.france24.com/en/africa/20251014-madagascar-rajoelina-assassination-attempt'>FRANCE 24</a>)</li><li>Youth-led protesters: Demonstrators want Rajoelina to step down and have focused their energy on pushing for immediate change. (<a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/Scenting-victory-Madagascar-youth-give-scant-thought-to-whats-next'>The Straits Times</a>)</li><li>CAPSAT elite unit: The unit joined the protests and called for the president and ministers to resign. (<a href='http://www.euronews.com/2025/10/14/madagascar-president-flees-country-after-military-unit-joins-anti-government-protests'>Euronews</a>)</li><li>French presidency: President Emmanuel Macron offered support to Rajoelina after he left with French assistance, according to reporting. (<a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/le-monde-africa/article/2025/10/14/madagascar-s-president-clings-to-power-as-macron-offers-support_6746411_124.html'>Le Monde</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/Madagascar-president-dissolves-national-assembly-escalating-crisis'>Madagascar president dissolves national assembly, escalating crisis</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.npr.org/2025/10/13/nx-s1-5573511/madagascar-president-flees-country-military-rebellion'>Madagascar&#x27;s president flees country in fear for his life after military rebellion</a> - npr.org</li><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2025/oct/13/madagascar-president-andry-rajoelina-flees-country-capsat'>Madagascar president says he fled country in fear for